37:06.891 --> 37:10.228 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I believe the price per
pound is going
to become so low that the
industry is going

37:10.261 --> 37:11.996 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to be driven out of Humboldt
County

37:12.030 --> 37:16.734 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PATRICK MURPHY: The fear is that
the people
that were a part of this, that
started this

37:16.768 --> 37:20.171 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
movement will not have a place
in the future.

37:20.205 --> 37:25.844 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it will only happen if we do
not take
part, if we do not stand up and
make our voices

37:25.877 --> 37:28.346 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
heard as the heart and soul of
the cannabis
industry.

37:28.379 --> 37:38.890 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SHERAZ SADIQ: For the "PBS
NewsHour," I'm
Sheraz Sadiq in Humboldt County,
California.

37:38.923 --> 37:49.367 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Now we
continue our series
on the best of the year in arts
-- tonight,

37:49.400 --> 37:51.035 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
what stood out in the world of
movies.

37:51.069 --> 37:52.804 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Jeffrey Brown is back with our
conversation.

37:52.837 --> 37:57.008 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: And for that, we
are joined
again by two of our steadfast
and stalwart

37:57.041 --> 38:02.247 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
film critics, Ann Hornaday of
The Washington
Post and Mike Sargent of
Pacifica Radio.

38:02.280 --> 38:03.481 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Welcome back to both of you.

38:03.515 --> 38:04.649 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ANN HORNADAY, Film Critic, The
Washington
Post: Thank you.

38:04.682 --> 38:06.017 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MIKE SARGENT, Film Critic,
Pacifica Radio:
Thank you.

38:06.050 --> 38:07.085 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: So, let's start
with a quick
roundup, a top five.

38:07.118 --> 38:08.620 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Then we will go into a little
bit more detail.

38:08.653 --> 38:09.621 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Ann.

38:09.654 --> 38:11.489 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
ANN HORNADAY: OK, top five.

38:11.523 --> 38:15.360 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Number one, "Moonlight," Barry
Jenkins' coming
of age story, "Manchester by the
Sea," wonderful

38:15.393 --> 38:20.899 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
domestic drama by Kenneth
Lonergan, "Hell
or High Water," a terrific
contemporary Western,

38:20.932 --> 38:26.204 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a little father-son serial comic
drama called
"The Confirmation" Clive Owen,
and then finally

38:26.237 --> 38:28.907 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
"O.J.: Made in America," the
amazing O.J.
Simpson documentary.

38:28.940 --> 38:31.709 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Which also made
our television
list, but that had a film
release.

38:31.743 --> 38:32.744 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ANN HORNADAY: Indeed.

38:32.777 --> 38:34.145 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: OK, Mike Sargent,
your top
five.

38:34.179 --> 38:35.914 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MIKE SARGENT: Well, my top five.

38:35.947 --> 38:40.118 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The top one is a film called
"Arrival," which
is a science fiction about
aliens landing

38:40.151 --> 38:41.920 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and us trying to communicate.

38:41.953 --> 38:46.191 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Then there's Mel Gibson's
"Hacksaw Ridge,"
which is about Desmond Doss, who
won the Medal

38:46.224 --> 38:49.661 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of Honor without ever having to
fire one bullet.

38:49.694 --> 38:52.463 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Then I have "Purge: Election
Year," which
is the third film in the series.

38:52.497 --> 38:58.369 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But the Purge is something that
happens once
a year in this future dystopian
America where

38:58.403 --> 39:02.640 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
once a year you get to purge,
and violence
is legal for 24 hours.

39:02.674 --> 39:07.378 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And this film actually does what
the premise
should have done in the first
two films, and

39:07.412 --> 39:08.846 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I really like it.

39:08.880 --> 39:13.084 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Then I have "Moonlight," which I
love just
probably as much as Ann did.

39:13.117 --> 39:16.888 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And then a film that I almost
forgot called
"Eye in the Sky" with Helen
Mirren, which

39:16.921 --> 39:21.326 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
is the final performance of Alan
Rickman,
but it's a film not to be
missed.

39:21.359 --> 39:23.561 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Let's watch a
little clip from
"Moonlight."

39:23.595 --> 39:26.297 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Then we will talk a little bit
more about
it.

39:26.331 --> 39:28.299 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ACTRESS: What's wrong?

39:28.333 --> 39:29.634 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
ACTOR: Nothing.

39:29.667 --> 39:30.969 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I'm good.

39:31.002 --> 39:32.337 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
ACTRESS: No.

39:32.370 --> 39:34.606 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I have seen good.

39:34.639 --> 39:36.674 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And you ain't it.

39:36.708 --> 39:41.446 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Stop putting your head down in
my house.

39:41.479 --> 39:43.948 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
You know my rule.

39:43.982 --> 39:48.486 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's all love and all pride in
this house.

39:48.519 --> 39:50.321 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
You feel me?

39:50.355 --> 39:52.890 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: All right, so,
Ann, an unusual
film in many ways, episodic,
takes one man

39:52.924 --> 39:54.359 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
through three different actors.

39:54.392 --> 39:55.426 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ANN HORNADAY: Yes.

39:55.460 --> 39:57.195 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Indeed, exactly.

39:57.228 --> 40:01.733 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's a young boy's story, as you
said, told
in three distinct chapters,
first when he

40:01.766 --> 40:06.237 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is a young boy, then as a
teenager and then
as a young man.

40:06.271 --> 40:14.646 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it's about a person coming
of age in poverty,
in this case in Liberty City,
Miami.

40:14.679 --> 40:20.618 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That scene that we just saw
features Janelle
Monae in an absolute breakout
performance.

40:20.652 --> 40:23.988 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And she's also in another movie
that is out
right now called "Hidden
Figures."

40:24.022 --> 40:27.925 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Known, first of
all, as a singer,
a musician, and now suddenly a
great actress.

40:27.959 --> 40:28.926 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ANN HORNADAY: Exactly.

40:28.960 --> 40:30.795 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
She's just a great actress.

40:30.828 --> 40:38.236 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it's just -- it's a very
tender, observant
-- as Mike said, it takes all
the kind of

40:38.269 --> 40:43.941 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
tropes of a coming of age story
and turns
them inside out and makes them
so intimate.

40:43.975 --> 40:50.148 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And Jenkins' kind of -- his
point of view
is just a little askance, it's a
little askew,

40:50.181 --> 40:53.418 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
so that you're not getting the
conventional
beats of a person's life.

40:53.451 --> 40:57.488 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You're getting the in-between
times, which
are sometimes even more
meaningful.

40:57.522 --> 40:59.791 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: All right, Mike,
you singled
out "Arrival."

40:59.824 --> 41:02.026 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, let's take a look at a scene
from that.

41:02.060 --> 41:04.195 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
AMY ADAMS, Actress: I need to
see me.

41:04.228 --> 41:06.264 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ACTOR: She's walking toward the
screen.

41:06.297 --> 41:17.108 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
AMY ADAMS: Now, that's a proper
introduction.

41:17.141 --> 41:30.588 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: So, what do you
love about
"Arrival," Mike?

41:30.621 --> 41:33.624 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MIKE SARGENT: I love pretty much
about pretty
much everything about this film.

41:33.658 --> 41:38.162 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's a film that does what
science fiction
and good science fiction should
be, where

41:38.196 --> 41:40.398 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
it says a lot about the human
condition.

41:40.431 --> 41:45.136 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This is a film that deals with
the issues
of communication, how and why we
communicate,

41:45.169 --> 41:50.708 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
what the nature of that is, what
the issues
are between nations, how we
don't get along

41:50.742 --> 41:53.277 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and are on the verge of war
throughout the
story.

41:53.311 --> 41:59.250 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And it deals with time and just
how we -- what
our relationship is to time.

41:59.283 --> 42:03.421 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The movie is in many ways like a
large "Twilight
Zone" episode.

42:03.454 --> 42:05.189 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
But it's beautifully shot.

42:05.223 --> 42:07.458 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's beautifully acted.

42:07.492 --> 42:11.295 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The aliens are very powerful and
meaningful.

42:11.329 --> 42:16.134 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I don't want to give too
much away, but
the way in which the aliens
communicate is

42:16.167 --> 42:22.073 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
such in an imaginative -- and
it's just a
beautiful film that to me works
on every level.

42:22.106 --> 42:25.743 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: All right, so we
asked both
of you also to pick an acting
performance

42:25.777 --> 42:28.012 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that stood out for you this
year.

42:28.045 --> 42:31.482 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, Ann, you chose Casey
Affleck in "Manchester
by the Sea."

42:31.516 --> 42:32.750 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Let's take a quick look.

42:32.784 --> 42:36.154 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
CASEY AFFLECK, Actor: I don't
understand.

42:36.187 --> 42:44.362 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ACTOR: Which part are you having
trouble with?

42:44.395 --> 42:51.002 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
CASEY AFFLECK: Well, I can't be
the guardian.

42:51.035 --> 42:52.069 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
ACTOR: Well...

42:52.103 --> 42:53.571 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
CASEY AFFLECK: I mean, I can't.

42:53.604 --> 42:58.009 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ACTOR: Well, naturally, I
assumed Joe had
discussed all of this with you.

42:58.042 --> 43:01.078 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
CASEY AFFLECK: No, he didn't.

43:01.112 --> 43:02.079 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
No.

43:02.113 --> 43:04.215 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: What about it?

43:04.248 --> 43:05.283 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
What stood out there?

43:05.316 --> 43:06.784 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ANN HORNADAY: It's a very
interior performance.

43:06.818 --> 43:11.088 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The thing about Lonergan's
movies is that
they're really about subtext.

43:11.122 --> 43:14.492 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And when a movie is really about
subtext,
the actor has to bring it.

43:14.525 --> 43:18.896 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The actor has to provide for the
audience
all the things, the subterranean
emotions

43:18.930 --> 43:22.366 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and feelings that are going on
underneath
the dialogue, as we just saw in
that scene.

43:22.400 --> 43:24.235 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And Affleck does it just
brilliantly.

43:24.268 --> 43:27.738 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: All right, Mike,
and you picked
Viola Davis in "Fences," which
is the Denzel

43:27.772 --> 43:31.275 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Washington-directed film of the
August Wilson
play.

43:31.309 --> 43:33.077 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Let's look at a clip from that.

43:33.110 --> 43:35.580 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DENZEL WASHINGTON, Actor: It's
not easy for
me to admit that I have been
standing in the

43:35.613 --> 43:36.881 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
same place for 18 years.

43:36.914 --> 43:37.748 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
VIOLA DAVIS, Actress: Well, I
have been standing
with you.

43:37.782 --> 43:38.616 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I have been right here with you,
Troy.

43:38.649 --> 43:40.017 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I got a life, too.

43:40.051 --> 43:41.018 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I got 18 years of my life just
standing in
the same spot as you.

43:41.052 --> 43:43.354 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Don't you think I ever wanted
other things?

43:43.387 --> 43:52.697 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Don't you think I had dreams and
hopes?

43:52.730 --> 43:57.702 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
What about my life?

43:57.735 --> 43:58.703 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
What about me?

43:58.736 --> 44:00.438 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: All right, Mike,
Viola Davis.

44:00.471 --> 44:01.105 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MIKE SARGENT: Well, Viola Davis,
I have to
say, is just one of those
actresses who is

44:01.138 --> 44:02.106 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
transformative.

44:02.140 --> 44:04.942 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
She becomes the character who
she is in this.

44:04.976 --> 44:10.181 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This is based on the play by
August Wilson,
and it's first in a series, a
series of plays

44:10.214 --> 44:14.018 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that he's done about black life
in America
during a specific period.

44:14.051 --> 44:19.590 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And Viola Davis is, though she's
probably
going to be nominated as best
supporting actress

44:19.624 --> 44:23.794 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
for this, she really, whenever
she's on screen,
she just takes it.

44:23.828 --> 44:24.795 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
She's won an Emmy.

44:24.829 --> 44:26.664 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
She's won a Tony.

44:26.697 --> 44:29.700 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think she may be one of
those few actors
who is going win all three and
win an Oscar.

44:29.734 --> 44:33.471 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She is just -- she is not just
someone who
just you watch you act.

44:33.504 --> 44:34.539 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
She moves you.

44:34.572 --> 44:36.340 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And she really does in this
film.

44:36.374 --> 44:39.143 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: All right, how
just quickly,
before we go, give us something
that maybe

44:39.176 --> 44:41.812 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
we just missed altogether that
you want to
recommend to us.

44:41.846 --> 44:44.482 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MIKE SARGENT: Well, I would
recommend a film
called "Tanna."

44:44.515 --> 44:46.284 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
That'S T-A-N-N-A.

44:46.317 --> 44:52.223 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
"Tanna" is essentially a Romeo
and Juliet
story, but it's told by an
indigenous people,

44:52.256 --> 44:54.058 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
indigenous actors.

44:54.091 --> 44:57.628 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's actually Australia's entry
for the Oscars
and it made the short list for
best foreign

44:57.662 --> 44:59.330 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
film this year.

44:59.363 --> 45:01.232 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It's a beautifully shot film.

45:01.265 --> 45:06.170 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's in another language, but so
much of it
is about the dialogue and what
goes on.

45:06.203 --> 45:10.207 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They're star-crossed lovers in a
tribe where
you can't get together.

45:10.241 --> 45:13.010 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I have to say it's just --
it's an amazing
film.

45:13.044 --> 45:14.512 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: All right, Ann
Hornaday.

45:14.545 --> 45:16.781 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ANN HORNADAY: This is a tough
one because
there were a lot this year.

45:16.814 --> 45:20.384 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But one that I really loved
watching was called
"A Bigger Splash."

45:20.418 --> 45:23.754 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's from the Italian director
Luca Guadagnino.

45:23.788 --> 45:25.189 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I think that's how you pronounce
his name.

45:25.222 --> 45:26.924 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

45:26.958 --> 45:30.595 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ANN HORNADAY: It stars Tilda
Swinton as a
rock star who is rusticating in
Italy with

45:30.628 --> 45:34.432 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
her boyfriend/husband, I think,
who is a filmmaker.

45:34.465 --> 45:35.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
She has laryngitis.

45:35.800 --> 45:36.434 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Sound horrible,
right, a horrible
life, right?

45:36.467 --> 45:37.435 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(CROSSTALK)

45:37.468 --> 45:38.436 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ANN HORNADAY: No, it is just so
luxurious.

45:38.469 --> 45:39.437 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And the scenery is beautiful.

45:39.470 --> 45:40.771 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: That's what I
meant.

45:40.805 --> 45:42.206 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The clothes are beautiful, and
