ways, and particularly
encouraging to young women
journalists of

47:06.157 --> 47:07.124 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
color.

47:07.158 --> 47:08.259 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Have a listen.

47:08.292 --> 47:10.561 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
YAMICHE ALCINDOR, The New York
Times: Dear,
Gwen.

47:10.594 --> 47:12.897 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
HANNAH ALLAM, McClatchy
Newspapers: Dear,
Gwen.

47:12.930 --> 47:14.865 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
TANZINA VEGA, CNN: Dear, Gwen.

47:14.899 --> 47:16.834 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
KAT CHOW, NPR: Dear, Gwen.

47:16.867 --> 47:18.769 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
YAMICHE ALCINDOR: Thank you for
telling that
you know my name.

47:18.803 --> 47:24.575 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HANNAH ALLAM: For the time that
I showed up
to your studio with straight
hair, because

47:24.608 --> 47:26.844 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
everybody knows this isn't
polished.

47:26.877 --> 47:31.215 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
YAMICHE ALCINDOR: I think of
just knowing
myself and knowing my name and
owning who

47:31.248 --> 47:32.216 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
I am.

47:32.249 --> 47:34.018 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And it was so important that you
told me that.

47:34.051 --> 47:39.090 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HANNAH ALLAM: You gave me a look
that was
something like, and then you
said, "You know,

47:39.123 --> 47:41.258 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
you don't have to do that here."

47:41.292 --> 47:47.465 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
That meant the world to me.

47:47.498 --> 47:55.639 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KAT CHOW: When you're young, you
don't really
think about how important it is
to see people

47:55.673 --> 47:59.577 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
who are a woman or a woman of
color in those
positions.

47:59.610 --> 48:04.415 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TANZINA VEGA: You were a beacon
for so many
of us, women of color
especially, who wanted

48:04.448 --> 48:07.284 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
so badly to see themselves
reflected in the
media.

48:07.318 --> 48:12.790 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KAT CHOW: I only saw older white
guys on TV
behind the anchor desk.

48:12.823 --> 48:16.327 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAMELA KIRKLAND: But there you
were, a beacon
of hope in a sea of white faces.

48:16.360 --> 48:21.098 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
YAMICHE ALCINDOR: The fact that
you were covering
the White House, that meant
something.

48:21.132 --> 48:25.436 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That meant I could go and pursue
the career
and become a journalist.

48:25.469 --> 48:28.639 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NIA-MALIKA HENDERSON, CNN: All
of the young
journalists of color, women
particularly,

48:28.672 --> 48:30.307 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
we all looked to you as an
example.

48:30.341 --> 48:33.944 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAMELA KIRKLAND: I can remember
when I interviewed
for this job at "NewsHour."

48:33.978 --> 48:36.313 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And they asked me why I wanted
to work here.

48:36.347 --> 48:39.183 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And for me, the answer was
simple: It was
you.

48:39.216 --> 48:43.754 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HANNAH ALLAM: I remember, at the
Gridiron
Dinner a few years ago, you
pulled me aside

48:43.788 --> 48:45.222 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and said, "What are you covering
now?"

48:45.256 --> 48:47.758 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And I said "foreign policy."

48:47.792 --> 48:49.994 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And your eyes lit up and you
said: "Great.

48:50.027 --> 48:53.931 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I need more people of color to
come on the
show and talk about foreign
policy."

48:53.964 --> 48:58.068 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NIA-MALIKA HENDERSON: I just
knew I had made
it when I was on "Washington
Week With Gwen

48:58.102 --> 49:02.740 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Ifill," because you knew the
folks on "Gwen
Ifill," that, Gwen, you
respected them.

49:02.773 --> 49:11.182 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And to have your respect in that
moment on
those shows, it was everything.

49:11.215 --> 49:23.961 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KRISSAH THOMPSON, The Washington
Post: You,
a successful as you were, and as
prominent,

49:23.994 --> 49:27.998 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
read my work and took the time
to encourage
me.

49:28.032 --> 49:29.867 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JASMINE WRIGHT: You saw me.

49:29.900 --> 49:35.539 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You saw me for who I was, and
you were proud
of me.

49:35.573 --> 49:48.285 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAMELA KIRKLAND: I have admired
you and Judy
Woodruff for showing me that two
female co-anchors

49:48.319 --> 49:50.221 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
could be a norm, instead of the
exception.

49:50.254 --> 49:55.059 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KAT CHOW: Now, more than ever,
we're at a
place where we need journalists
like us.

49:55.092 --> 49:56.861 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
TANZINA VEGA: We owe you our
gratitude.

49:56.894 --> 50:04.134 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HANNAH ALLAM: So, as I stand
here with tears
in my eyes thinking of how much
we have lost

50:04.168 --> 50:05.369 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
with your passing...

50:05.402 --> 50:06.937 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAMELA KIRKLAND: There will
never be another
Gwen Ifill.

50:06.971 --> 50:09.006 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
There will never be another you.

50:09.039 --> 50:12.543 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HANNAH ALLAM: We will miss your
journalism,
all of us.

50:12.576 --> 50:17.781 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
YAMICHE ALCINDOR: Dear, Gwen, I
am going to
really, really, really, really
miss you, but

50:17.815 --> 50:20.818 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
